# Co-located feature `_lib`

Do **not** add files under `apps/frontend/src/lib/`. Put helpers, stores, and domain logic next to the feature that owns them in a `_lib/` folder.

## Where code lives

| Owner | Path | Examples |
|-------|------|----------|
| Base UI primitives | `components/base/_lib/` | `utils.ts`, `image-source.ts` |
| Landing / storefront shell | `app/(landing)/_lib/` | `storefront-layout.ts` |
| Auth | `app/auth/_lib/` | `return-url.ts` |
| Global auth state | `providers/_lib/` | `auth-store.ts` |
| Admin | `app/admin/_lib/` | `admin-products-store.ts` |
| Cart | `app/cart/_lib/` | `cart-store.ts`, `cart-utils.ts` |
| Checkout | `app/checkout/_lib/` | `checkout-store.ts`, `checkout-data.ts` |
| Products | `app/products/_lib/` | `product-catalog.ts`, `product-detail.ts` |
| Profile | `app/profile/_lib/` | `favorites-store.ts`, `notifications-store.ts` |

## Import style

```tsx
// ✅ Feature-owned module
import { useCartStore } from '@/app/cart/_lib/cart-store';
import { cn } from '@/components/base/_lib/utils';

// ❌ Central lib (removed)
import { useCartStore } from '@/lib/cart-store';
```

## Cross-feature imports

When another route needs logic from a feature, import from that feature's `_lib` explicitly (e.g. checkout importing `@/app/cart/_lib/cart-store`). Do not copy or re-export through a shared root folder.

## Adding new logic

1. Identify the owning route/feature (cart, checkout, admin, etc.).
2. Add the file under that feature's `_lib/` folder.
3. If it is only used by base components, put it in `components/base/_lib/`.
4. If it is app-wide provider state, put it in `providers/_lib/`.
